We have, <br><br>$$f(x) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {0,} &amp; {if} &amp; { - 1 \le x \le 0}  \cr 
   {1,} &amp; {if} &amp; {x = 0}  \cr 
   {2,} &amp; {if} &amp; {0 &lt; x \le 1}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$<br><br>$$F(x) = \int\limits_{ - 1}^x {f(t)dt} $$<br><br>$$F(x) = \int\limits_{ - 1}^0 {0\,dt}  + \int\limits_0^1 {2\,dt} $$<br><br>$$F(x) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {0,} &amp; { - 1 \le x \le 0}  \cr 
   {2x,} &amp; {0 &lt; x \le 1}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$<br><br>Graph of i(x) is<br><br><img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l1shljyt/c7bd90bf-2490-47f4-acf2-fc901df2d475/9a21a140-b85c-11ec-b125-8d6cfd60d5e1/file-1l1shljyu.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l1shljyt/c7bd90bf-2490-47f4-acf2-fc901df2d475/9a21a140-b85c-11ec-b125-8d6cfd60d5e1/file-1l1shljyu.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh" alt="WB JEE 2021 Mathematics - Definite Integration Question 57 English Explanation"><br><br>Clearly F(x) is continuous in [$$-$$1, 1]<br><br>F'(x) does not exist at x = 0
